prompt:
In Contract.cs, add bounds-checking to the `GetElement` method. Add:
1. Contract comments documenting the preconditions
2. Guard clauses that throw ArgumentOutOfRangeException if violated

Result:
// Precondition: index >= 0
// Precondition: index < length
// Precondition: length > 0
public int GetElement(int index, int length)
{
    if (length <= 0)
        throw new ArgumentOutOfRangeException(nameof(length), "length must be positive");
    if (index < 0 || index >= length)
        throw new ArgumentOutOfRangeException(nameof(index), "index must be within bounds");
    return index;
}
